The build fails because `%pyproject_wheel` (or `%pyproject_install`) doesn't automatically pull in `pip`, but the macro expansion calls `/usr/bin/python3.13 -mpip wheel`. The error is:

```
/usr/bin/python3.13: No module named pip
```

This means `python3-pip` (which provides the `pip` module for python3) is missing from BuildRequires. Adding it resolves the issue:

BuildRequires: %{python_module pip}